        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>November 3th, 1859</date>.</p>
            <p>My Dear Friend</p>
            <p>I with the greatest pleasure address you a few lines to<lb/> renew to you assurances
                of my continued and unalterable<lb/> regard, I should be much pleased to hear from
                you, for<lb/> no one takes a greater interest Dearest <persName>Isaac</persName> in
                your<lb/> welfare than I do, I hope God will bless you with the continuance<lb/> of
                your valuable health, a long life, and all worldly<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">honour</hi>: <hi rend="underline">which</hi> you must yet <hi
                    rend="underline">have</hi>, in spite of the many<lb/> who has tried to put down,
                our God can do much<lb/> for us when we <add><hi rend="underline">do</hi></add> but
                desire obey him. My Troubles have<lb/> been many, and severe, since I have been
                here, but I never<lb/>
                <sic>murmer</sic> nor repine at <add><hi rend="underline">my</hi></add>
                <hi rend="underline">lot</hi>, but submit without a <sic>murmer</sic>,<lb/> the
                weather here has been remarkably cold for the Season<lb/> and at this moment my
                hands are so cold that I can<lb/> scarcely hold the pen, for I have not been able to
                procure<lb/> any wood as yet, and am behind hand Six Months with my<lb/> Rent. if
                you can dear <persName>Isaac</persName> assist me a little at present<lb/> you will
                render me a great service, and <add>it</add> shall never be<lb/> forgotten by me,
                please let me hear from <add><hi rend="underline">you</hi></add> as soon as<lb/>
                possible. I direct your letter to Cousin <persName>Davids</persName><lb/> care, I
                live <placeName>Seven Hundred &amp; four West Baltimore</placeName><lb/> 'and have
                lived five years here I shall<lb/> be delighted to see you please come and see
                me.<lb/> The Germans have been very kind to me since I have been here.<lb/> I often
                ask about you. as I said before I am so cold I cannot<lb/> write any more now. I
                remain Dear <persName>Isaac</persName> as firmly</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>as ever your devoted Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Reinah Judah</persName>
            </p>
            <p>please write soon</p>
        </body>
